Here's a PlantUML component diagram capturing the static architecture of the gr-corrsounder system, focusing on the general architectural concern:

```plantuml
@startuml inIT-HF_gr-corrsounder

skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor<<GNU Radio>> LightGreen
  BackgroundColor<<C++>> LightBlue
  BackgroundColor<<Python>> Yellow
}

package "gr-corrsounder" {
  [GNU Radio Blocks] <<C++>> as GRBlocks
  [SWIG Bindings] as SWIG
  [Python Wrappers] <<Python>> as PyWrappers
  [pycorrsounder] <<Python>> as PyCorrsounder
  [GRC XML Definitions] as GRC
  [Unit Tests] as Tests
  [CMake Build System] as CMake
  [Documentation] as Docs
  
  component "Channel Sounding Blocks" as CSBlocks {
    [Sequence Generation]
    [Correlation]
    [Error Correction]
    [Moving Average]
    [Sequence Gate]
    [Ramdisk File Sink]
    [IR SNR]
    [FZC Source]
    [FZC Correlator]
  }
}

[GNU Radio Framework] <<GNU Radio>> as GNURadio

GRBlocks --> CSBlocks : implements
SWIG --> GRBlocks : wraps
PyWrappers --> SWIG : uses
GRC --> GRBlocks : describes
Tests --> GRBlocks : validates
Tests --> PyCorrsounder : validates
CMake --> GRBlocks : builds
CMake --> SWIG : builds
CMake --> PyWrappers : builds
CMake --> PyCorrsounder : builds
Docs --> GRBlocks : describes
GNURadio --> GRBlocks : uses
PyWrappers --> GNURadio : integrates with
PyCorrsounder --> PyWrappers : supports

@enduml
```